### Description

Calling the effect cleanup multiple times inside the effect function only considers the last cleanup one. I don't know whether it is a bug or missing feature. Till today i thought it is supported similar to `DestroyRef`.

```ts

class TestComponent {
    constructor() {
        effect((onCleanup) => {
            const target = this.target();
            ....
            const resizeObserver = new ResizeObserver(() => {
                ....
            });
            resizeObserver.observe(target());
            onCleanup(() => resizeObserver.disconnect());

            if (checkScroll) {
                target.addEventListener('scroll', this.updateDimension);
                onCleanup(() => target.removeEventListener('scroll', this.updateDimension)); // Only this cleanup gets called
            }
        });
    }
}
```


